The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, April 25, 2004 				 Another arrest in Santiniketan
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								Santiniketan, April 24: One more person has been arrested in connection with the theft of a sandalwood tree from the Visva-Bharati University complex. After arresting Sheikh Akhtar, who confessed to the crime, police nabbed his son, Afroz, on Friday. 																								A sandalwood tree was stolen in mid-January from near the Uttarayan complex housing the Rabindranath Memorial Museum, and the police suspect that the same gang might have had a hand in the Nobel medal heist as well. Afroz confessed to being in cahoots with his father and has been taken into custody for seven days. 																								He sold the sandalwood tree stolen by his father. He is involved in the business. Afroz has given us some important information which will help in solving the Tagore heist case, a senior police official said. 																								In another development, a CBI constable investigating the medal theft died in an accident near Santiniketan, giving rise to speculation that it could be murder. 
